{{Quote|I don't believe these are bugs, Captain Solo. They appear to be a sentient hybrid of coleoptera and hymenoptera, which often use complex dances as a means of communication.|[[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] to [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]]|<ref name="Dark Nest I: The Joiner King">''[[Dark Nest I: The Joiner King]]''</ref>}}
The [[Killik/Legends|Killik]] [[Species/Legends|species]] used a very complex '''language''' to communicate, far more sophisticated than [[Galactic Basic Standard/Legends|Basic]] or [[Shyriiwook/Legends|Shyriiwook]]. The insects raised and lowered their abdomen, rapidly shut their mandibles and rubbed antennae together to convey their language. This language was incomprehensible to [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]] when the [[Millennium Falcon/Legends|''Millennium Falcon'']] first encountered the Killiks, and only the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] were able to communicate fluently with the [[Alien/Legends|alien]] species.

